snippet.textDisplay: Ok, slightly douchy cabin fever question coming, but who actually isn't quarantined? Everyone in my social network has been doing it for weeks, it seems like it's the case no matter how far I delve into friends of friends and whatnot, but everything just seems to be getting worse no matter how long society stays in absolute lockdown and the media is suggesting that not a lot of people are quarantined or doing their part is a main reason why. Does anyone have any kind of examples of this in their life? Because I've been stuck at home with no work, little entertainment, and I can't remember the last in person conversation I had that wasn't with my dad. I'm losing my marbles and honestly any kind of indication that things are as people say they are would make this whole thing a lot less frustrating.
